    {
      "id": "eed072f464534f0ec1d20a640f6e44845afdfb60",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-29 03:34:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nwe are not really running acceptance-small during our test runs, so is there any benefit in this removal?\n\nI thought there is still hope we'll fix up liblustre at some point in time after 2.2?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "dae1ae3bd02eb564bdba3f56c65e0daaa2b15248",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-29 03:52:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI still use acc-sm for running my own tests, I'm not sure if others do as well.  It is also documented in many external locations as the default test suite to run for patches.\n\nRunning \"auster\" doesn't really provide any list of tests to run, nor is there a so I don't consider it a useful test script for most developers.  I would have no objection to acc-sm becoming a wrapper around \"auster\" that just supplied a list of tests for it to run, but that should be done in a separate patch, IMHO.\n\nIn any case, it is misleading for external developers (e.g. EMC) to include liblustre in acc-sm if it does not pass, and if there are only a few people using acc-sm today then there is also little harm in landing the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "5d8579ea1de290b2a3fd069cd8f281f52348ac59",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-04-07 01:32:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
